'''数字版权管理'''（{{lang-en|Digital rights management}}，縮寫為'''DRM'''）是一系列[[访问控制|访问控制]]技术<ref name="act11">{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0rVfRwcIPYgC&pg=SA9-PA26&dq=DRM+%22access+control+technology%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Jv6IUZ3RJZT09gSI04HYCA&ved=0CEAQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=DRM%20%22access%20control%20technology%22&f=false|title=Computer Forensics: Investigating Network Intrusions and Cybercrime|publisher=[[Cengage_Learning|Cengage Learning]]|pages=9–26|access-date=2014-04-03|archive-date=2014-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405045506/http://books.google.com/books?id=0rVfRwcIPYgC&pg=SA9-PA26&dq=DRM+%22access+control+technology%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Jv6IUZ3RJZT09gSI04HYCA&ved=0CEAQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=DRM%20%22access%20control%20technology%22&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="act2">{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ntsJqzfwFhkC&pg=PA302&dq=DRM+%22access+control+technology%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Jv6IUZ3RJZT09gSI04HYCA&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=DRM%20%22access%20control%20technology%22&f=false|title=Multimedia Networking: From Theory to Practice|author=Hwang, Jenq-Neng|publisher=[[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]|year=2009|page=410|access-date=2014-04-03|archive-date=2014-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405045218/http://books.google.com/books?id=ntsJqzfwFhkC&pg=PA302&dq=DRM+%22access+control+technology%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Jv6IUZ3RJZT09gSI04HYCA&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=DRM%20%22access%20control%20technology%22&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>，通常用于控制数字内容和设备在被销售之后的使用过程<ref name="Ross">{{cite book|url=http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~rja14/book.html|title=Security Engineering|publisher=WILEY|chapter=22: Copyright and DRM|access-date=2014-04-03|archive-date=2011-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226114349/http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~rja14/book.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WillStep">{{cite book | url=http://www.giantstepsmts.com/digitalrightsbookpreface.htm | title=Digital Rights Management: Business and Technology | publisher=M&T Books | chapter=The Changing Attitude Toward DRM | access-date=2014-04-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205094540/http://www.giantstepsmts.com/digitalrightsbookpreface.htm | archive-date=2013-12-05 | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=827994 Digital rights management for content distribution] {{Wayback|url=http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=827994 |date=20160414002551 }}. Dl.acm.org. Retrieved on 2013-07-29.</ref>。DRM有时也称为[[复制保护|拷贝保护]]、复制控制、技术保护措施等，但这些稱呼存在争议<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=http://www.priv.gc.ca/resource/fs-fi/02_05_d_32_e.asp |title=Fact Sheet: Digital Rights Management and have to do: Technical Protection Measures (November 2006) |accessdate=2014-04-03 |archive-date=2016-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414002554/http://www.priv.gc.ca/resource/fs-fi/02_05_d_32_e.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref>。许多数字出版社和软件厂商都使用了DRM，例如[[Amazon.com|亞馬遜]]、[[AT&T|AT&T]]、[[AOL|AOL]]、[[Apple_Inc.|Apple Inc.]]、[[Netflix|Netflix]]、[[Google|Google]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://support.google.com/books/partner/answer/170424?hl=en+|title=DRM options for downloads of books on Google Play|date=March 6, 2013|accessdate=2013-04-29|publisher=Google}}</ref>、[[BBC|BBC]]、[[微軟|微軟]]、[[Sony|Sony]]、[[Valve_Corporation|Valve Corporation]](以及其旗下的[[Steam|Steam]])等。

== 簡介 ==
DRM控制带版权作品的使用、更改和分发，适用于软件、系统、音乐、电影等多媒体内容。<ref name=":0" />

DRM的使用存在争议。支持者认为和私有财产需要用锁来防止盗窃一样，[[知识财产|知识产权]]也需要DRM来防止未授权使用<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/the-pros-cons-and-future-of-drm-1.785237|title=The pros, cons, and future of DRM|author=|date=|work=|newspaper=CBC|accessdate=2018-07-16|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310091216/http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/the-pros-cons-and-future-of-drm-1.785237|dead-url=no}}</ref>，保护[[著作權|著作权]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.artistscope.com/protection.asp|title=Copy Protection for Images and the Internet|accessdate=2018-07-16|work=www.artistscope.com|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710121521/http://www.artistscope.com/protection.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref>并确保可持续的收入流<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.streamingmedia.com/r/printerfriendly.asp?id=8306|title=Making Money with Streaming Media|accessdate=|author=|date=2003-02-03|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060514024614/http://www.streamingmedia.com/r/printerfriendly.asp?id=8306|archivedate=2006-05-14}}</ref>。反对者则认为DRM无法有效阻止侵权，反而會造成正版用户不便，同时还可能使大公司阻碍竞争和创新。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eff.org/issues/drm|title=DRM|newspaper=Electronic Frontier Foundation|accessdate=2018-07-16|language=en|archive-date=2018-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705015859/https://www.eff.org/issues/drm|dead-url=no}}</ref>另外，一旦DRM提供商停止服务，使用DRM技術的产品很可能再也無法使用。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://opensource.com/life/11/11/drm-graveyard-brief-history-digital-rights-management-music|title=The DRM graveyard: A brief history of digital rights management in music|newspaper=Opensource.com|accessdate=2018-07-16|language=en|archive-date=2012-09-22|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AsIm8lhh?url=http://opensource.com/life/11/11/drm-graveyard-brief-history-digital-rights-management-music|dead-url=no}}</ref>DRM还可以用来限制用户合法权益，包括制作备份、出借给图书馆、使用公有领域作品、研究学习等[[合理使用|合理使用]]。<ref name=":1" />[[电子边界基金会|电子边界基金会]]和[[自由软件基金会|自由软件基金会]]都认为DRM是[[反竞争行为|反竞争行为]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eff.org/deeplinks/archives/001557.php|title=FairPlay: Another Anticompetitive Use of DRM|accessdate=2006-08-01|archive-date=2006-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060716215249/http://www.eff.org/deeplinks/archives/001557.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>自由软件基金会还建议把DRM这一缩写解释为「数字限制管理」（Digital Restrictions Management），因为「[[著作權|著作權]]」（rights）一词容易让人误解。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fsf.org/campaigns/drm.html|title=Digital Restrictions Management and Treacherous Computing — Free Software Foundation — working together for free software|accessdate=2018-07-16|work=www.fsf.org|language=en|archive-date=2018-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705233004/https://www.fsf.org/campaigns/drm.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

国际上，许多国家通-{}-过法律禁止绕过DRM，同时也禁止开发和传播相关工具、讨论相关方法和技巧。美国的[[數字千年版權法|数字千年版权法案]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/PLAW-105publ304/html/PLAW-105publ304.htm|title=Public Law 105 – 304 – Digital Millennium Copyright Act|accessdate=2018-07-16|author=|date=|publisher=U. S. Government Publishing Office.|archive-date=2018-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180716140639/https://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/PLAW-105publ304/html/PLAW-105publ304.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>和欧盟的[[Copyright_Directive|2001/29/EC版权指令]]<ref>{{Citation|title=Directive 2001/29/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 22 May 2001 on the harmonisation of certain aspects of copyright and related rights in the information society|date=2001-06-22|url=http://data.europa.eu/eli/dir/2001/29/oj/eng|volume=OJ L|issue=32001L0029|language=en|accessdate=2018-07-16}}</ref>中都包含这些条款。

== 历史 ==
随着数字媒体的普及，版权持有者开始担忧他们所处行业的命运，特别是在音乐和电影领域。基于[[模擬信號|模拟信号]]的传统媒體在复制时会出现无法避免的失真，而基于[[数字信号|数字信号]]的媒體文件则可以无损复制無數次。個人電腦的出現，以及網際網路和文件分享工具的流行，使得[[盗版|盗版]]日益普遍。{{Fact}}

1983年，日本工程师Ryoichi Mori设计了早期的DRM系统，称为软件服务系统（SSS）<ref>[http://v3.espacenet.com/publicationDetails/biblio?DB=EPODOC&adjacent=true&locale=en_EP&FT=D&date=19850501&CC=JP&NR=60077218A&KC=A Patent application 58-186100]（Publication #60-077218）, ''Software Control System'', Japan Patent Office, October 5, 1983, Ryoichi Mori, applicant. Reported by [[Industrial_Property_Digital_Library|Industrial Property Digital Library]].</ref>{{Dead link}}，之后的改进版又被命名为超级分发（superdistribution）。SSS基于密码学技术，由专门的硬件负责解密。在其设计理念中，不但不限制分发数字产品的加密版，反而会鼓励用户进行分享。

==技术==
===电影===
[[DVD论坛|DVD论坛]]的[[內容擾亂系統|内容扰乱系统]]是一个早期的DRM系统。它使用简单的[[加密|加密算法]]，制作DVD播放器的厂商必须获得授权在产品中实现此技术，然后才能解密并播放DVD中的加密内容。授权条款规定了播放DVD内容的方式，包括输出信号的格式和方式，以保证在电视上播放时视频的加密不受破坏。

1999年，[[Jon_Lech_Johansen|Jon Lech Johansen]]发布了[[DeCSS|DeCSS]]，一个在Linux系统上播放加密DVD的程序。当时Linux系统上还没有获得授权的DVD播放器，DeCSS的合法性也遭争议——开发者卷入了官司，分发密钥则受“[[非法質數|非法质数]]”限制。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://w2.eff.org/IP/Video/MPAA_DVD_cases/?f=20000202_ny_memorandum_order.html|title=Electronic Frontier Foundation|accessdate=2018-07-16|work=Electronic Frontier Foundation|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161213144005/https://w2.eff.org/IP/Video/MPAA_DVD_cases/?f=20000202_ny_memorandum_order.html|archive-date=2016-12-13|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

同样是在1999年，微软发布了[[Windows_Media_DRM|WMDRM]]，用于执行媒体文件包含的DRM指令，限制用户对媒体文件的使用。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~rja14/book.html|title=Security Engineering: A Guide to Building Dependable Distributed Systems|accessdate=2018-07-16|author=|date=|work=www.cl.cam.ac.uk|publisher=|archive-date=2011-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226114349/http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~rja14/book.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>这些DRM指令可以指定文件的播放次数、是否能被备份或转发。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.directionsonmicrosoft.com/sample/DOMIS/update/2003/04apr/0403rmctte.htm|title=Rights Management Comes to the Enterprise|author=|date=2003-03-17|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821220931/http://www.directionsonmicrosoft.com/sample/DOMIS/update/2003/04apr/0403rmctte.htm|archivedate=2012-08-21}}</ref>后续的WMDRM可以限制用户在设备之间传输文件<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/windows7/windows-media-player-drm-frequently-asked-questions|title=Windows Media Player DRM: frequently asked questions|accessdate=2018-07-16|author=|date=|work=windows.microsoft.com|publisher=|archive-date=2013-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806154306/http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/windows7/windows-media-player-drm-frequently-asked-questions|dead-url=no}}</ref>，实现了文件在过期后就无法再播放的订阅式服务，还实现了[[區域限制|区域限制]]。<ref name="Ross" />

[[Windows_Vista|Windows Vista]]系统内嵌的DRM系统名为[[受保护媒体路径|受保护媒体路径]]，其中包含了受保护视频路径（PVP）。当有未签名的软件运行时，PVP會停止播放使用DRM的影片，以阻止未知软件获取内容。另外，PVP可以加密向显示器或显卡传输的信息，让转录更加困难。

[[AACS|高级内容访问系统]]（Advanced Access Content System, AACS）是一个用于高清DVD和蓝光盘的DRM系统。它由AACS LA联盟开发，成员包括包括[[迪士尼|迪士尼]]、[[Intel|Intel]]、微軟、[[Panasonic|Panasonic]]、[[華納兄弟|華納兄弟]]、[[IBM|IBM]]、[[東芝|東芝]]和[[Sony|Sony]]。2006年12月，黑客在网上发布了一个密钥，可用于不受限地访问受AACS保护的高清DVD。<ref>{{cite web
